==== THE KDE CODE OF CONDUCT

(((KDE, Code of Conduct)))
When communicating in official KDE channels please observe the KDE Code of Conduct.
Our Code of Conduct presents a summary of the shared values and common sense thinking in
our community. The basic social ingredients that hold our project together include:

 * Be considerate

 * Be respectful

 * Be collaborative

 * Be pragmatic

Support others in the community
Get support from others in the community
The Code of Conduct can be found here : http://www.kde.org/code-of-conduct/
